text.tspan: Total COVID-19 tests conducted vs. Confirmed cases
A high number of confirmed cases for a given level of testing gives an indication that the number of confirmed
cases heavily underestimates the true number of infections. Comparisons across countries are affected by
differences in testing policies and reporting methods.
Source: Testing data from official sources collated by Our World in Data, confirmed cases from Johns Hopkins University CSSE
